---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import MoonPhaseCalculator from '../components/MoonPhaseCalculator.jsx';
---

<Layout
	title="Moon Phase Calculator — Today's Moon Phase & Any Date | Clockr"
	description="Find the moon phase for today or any date. See illumination, lunar cycle day, and days until the next full moon or new moon."
	category="seasons"
>
	<div class="sc-page">
		<div class="sc-header">
			<div class="sc-eyebrow">
				<span class="sc-eyebrow-square" aria-hidden="true"></span>
				SEASONS
			</div>
			<h1 class="sc-title">
				<span class="sc-gradient">Moon Phase Calculator</span>
			</h1>
			<p class="sc-subtitle">Find the moon phase for any date</p>
		</div>

		<MoonPhaseCalculator client:load />

		<!-- HOW IT WORKS -->
		<section class="sc-how">
			<h2 class="sc-section-title">How it works</h2>
			<div class="sc-how-card">
				<p>
					The Moon does not produce its own light — we see it because sunlight
					reflects off its surface. As the Moon orbits Earth, the angle between
					the Sun, Earth, and Moon changes, so the portion of the lit side we can
					see from Earth changes too. One complete cycle from new moon to new moon
					takes about 29.5 days, which is why moon phases follow a predictable
					monthly rhythm.
				</p>
				<p>
					This calculator uses a standard astronomical approximation: a known new
					moon at 18:14 UTC on 6 January 2000 as a reference point, plus a
					synodic month of 29.53058867 days. For any date, it works out how many
					days have elapsed since that reference, divides by the cycle length, and
					finds the position within the current cycle. From that position it
					derives the illumination percentage, phase name, and estimated days
					until the next full and new moons — no API or telescope required.
				</p>
				<p>
					Moon phases have long been used as a practical calendar in farming,
					fishing, and navigation, and they still influence coastal tides
					(alongside the Sun). Many cultures mark lunar festivals and folklore
					around the full moon. This tool gives a quick mathematical snapshot;
					for precise astronomical times to the minute, observatories use
					orbital models that account for the Moon's elliptical path.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- FAQ -->
		<section class="sc-faq">
			<h2 class="sc-section-title">Frequently asked questions</h2>
			<div class="sc-faq-list">
				<details class="sc-faq-item">
					<summary class="sc-faq-question">How often does a full moon occur?</summary>
					<div class="sc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Full moons occur once per synodic month — about every 29.5 days.
							That works out to roughly 12 full moons a year, with an occasional
							13th (a &ldquo;blue moon&rdquo; in the seasonal sense) when the
							timing of the cycle aligns that way. The exact date and time shift
							slightly each month because the Moon&apos;s orbit is not a perfect
							circle.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="sc-faq-item">
					<summary class="sc-faq-question"
						>Is the moon phase the same everywhere on Earth?</summary
					>
					<div class="sc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Yes — at any given moment, everyone on Earth sees the same moon
							phase. Someone in London and someone in Sydney both see a waxing
							gibbous (or whatever the phase is) at the same universal time. What
							changes by location is when the Moon rises and sets, and which way
							up it appears in the sky — not which fraction of the disc is lit.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="sc-faq-item">
					<summary class="sc-faq-question">How are moon phases calculated?</summary>
					<div class="sc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Clockr uses a synodic month of 29.53058867 days and a reference new
							moon at 18:14 UTC on 6 January 2000. Days since that reference are
							divided by the cycle length; the remainder is the Moon&apos;s age
							in the current cycle. Illumination comes from a cosine of that age,
							and the eight named phases are assigned by dividing the cycle into
							equal eighths.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="sc-faq-item">
					<summary class="sc-faq-question">How long is a lunar cycle?</summary>
					<div class="sc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							A synodic month — the time from one new moon to the next — averages
							about 29.53 days (29 days, 12 hours, and 44 minutes). That is
							slightly longer than the Moon&apos;s orbital period around Earth
							because Earth is also moving around the Sun, so the Sun–Moon angle
							takes longer to repeat.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- RELATED TOOLS -->
		<div class="sc-related">
			<h3 class="sc-related-title">Related tools</h3>
			<div class="sc-related-grid">
				<a href="/sun-calculator" class="sc-related-card"
					><span class="sc-related-name">Sun Calculator</span></a
				>
				<a href="/daylight-hours-calculator" class="sc-related-card"
					><span class="sc-related-name">Daylight Hours Calculator</span></a
				>
				<a href="/season-countdown" class="sc-related-card"
					><span class="sc-related-name">Season Countdown</span></a
				>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>

<style is:global>
	.sc-page {
		max-width: 800px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 60px 24px;
	}

	.sc-header {
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 32px;
	}

	.sc-eyebrow {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 8px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 3px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.sc-eyebrow-square {
		width: 8px;
		height: 8px;
		border-radius: 2px;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		flex-shrink: 0;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: initial;
	}

	.sc-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 64px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -3px;
		line-height: 1.05;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.sc-gradient {
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.sc-subtitle {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		line-height: 1.6;
	}

	.sc-section-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.sc-how {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.sc-how-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 24px;
	}

	.sc-how-card p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0 0 16px;
	}

	.sc-how-card p:last-child {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	.sc-faq {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.sc-faq-list {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 8px;
	}

	.sc-faq-item {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		overflow: hidden;
	}

	.sc-faq-question {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		font-weight: 600;
		padding: 18px 24px;
		cursor: pointer;
		list-style: none;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.sc-faq-question::-webkit-details-marker {
		display: none;
	}

	.sc-faq-question::after {
		content: '+';
		float: right;
		font-size: 18px;
		font-weight: 700;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.sc-faq-item[open] .sc-faq-question::after {
		content: '−';
	}

	.sc-faq-answer {
		padding: 0 24px 18px;
	}

	.sc-faq-answer p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.sc-related {
		border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		padding-top: 40px;
	}

	.sc-related-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.sc-related-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		gap: 12px;
	}

	.sc-related-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 20px 16px;
		text-align: center;
		text-decoration: none;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
	}

	.sc-related-card:hover {
		border-color: rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.4);
	}

	.sc-related-name {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	/* Moon Phase Calculator tool */
	.mpc-tool {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.mpc-date-wrap {
		max-width: 320px;
		margin: 0 auto 32px;
	}

	.mpc-hint {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);
		text-align: center;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.mpc-results {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 28px;
	}

	.mpc-hero {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		text-align: center;
		width: 100%;
		padding: 40px 24px;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0d1f17, #1a2e24);
		border: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.25);
		border-radius: 20px;
	}

	.mpc-moon-display {
		margin-bottom: 16px;
		filter: drop-shadow(0 0 28px rgba(116, 180, 155, 0.3));
		line-height: 0;
	}

	.mpc-moon-svg {
		display: block;
		width: clamp(96px, 22vw, 120px);
		height: auto;
	}

	.mpc-result-date {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		margin: 0 0 12px;
	}

	.mpc-phase-name {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: clamp(28px, 5vw, 40px);
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -1px;
		line-height: 1.1;
		margin: 0 0 8px;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.mpc-illumination {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 18px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.65);
		margin: 0;
	}

	.mpc-stats-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		gap: 12px;
		width: 100%;
	}

	@media (max-width: 560px) {
		.mpc-stats-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}

		.sc-title {
			font-size: 44px;
			letter-spacing: -2px;
		}

		.sc-related-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}

	.mpc-stat-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 24px 16px;
		text-align: center;
	}

	.mpc-stat-num {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 32px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -1px;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		margin-bottom: 6px;
	}

	.mpc-stat-label {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 11px;
		font-weight: 600;
		letter-spacing: 1px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.35);
	}

	.mpc-upcoming {
		width: 100%;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 12px;
	}

	.mpc-upcoming-row {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 4px;
		margin: 0;
		padding: 14px 16px;
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
	}

	.mpc-upcoming-label {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 11px;
		font-weight: 600;
		letter-spacing: 1.5px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.35);
	}

	.mpc-upcoming-date {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.75);
	}
</style>
